27/10/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- The NATO Military Committee, comprised of the permanent representatives of all 26 member states, arrived in Kosovo on Wednesday (26 October) to assess the situation in the province and the local interim institutions. Committee Chairman General Raymond Henault noted that the mechanisms for security and stability would be scrutinised, in light of the UN Security Council's recent decision to start status talks. 
In other news Wednesday, a vehicle carrying four Kosovo Serb police officers came under gunfire near the town of Kacanik in the south. None of the officers inside were wounded. This was the third attack targeting Serb policemen in the area in the last two months. (RTS - 27/10/05; Tanjug, KosovaLive, AP, Reuters - 26/10/05)
